		"Name": "Thug",
		"Details": "The\u00c2\u00a0Thug\u00c2\u00a0was designed by\u00c2\u00a0Maltex Corporation\u00c2\u00a0as a direct competitor to the popular\u00c2\u00a0Warhammer\u00c2\u00a0BattleMech. First seeing production in\u00c2\u00a02572, the\u00c2\u00a0Thug\u00c2\u00a0sought to directly address some of the challenges which faced the\u00c2\u00a0Warhammer, chief of which was to increase armor protection without sacrificing firepower. The Thugs long range striking power comes from a pair of arm mounted PPC\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s. Backing up the PPCs are two\u00c2\u00a0SRM-6\u00c2\u00a0launchers mounted in either side torso with one ton of\u00c2\u00a0CASE-protected reloads. Eighteen\u00c2\u00a0double heat sinks comfortably dissipate the enormous heat generated by the PPC\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s while an Endo Steel\u00c2\u00a0frame allows it to carry fifteen and a half tons of armor.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Accurate Weapon - Energy</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.14</color></b>",
